post_title: #8 PSA Registry Set - 521 all PSA Graded - Avg. 6+
post_content:
NLFS- consigned to Memory Lane to be sold as set break in Spring Auction 

The set is 521 cards -- this is the entire set, including a Maggie error PSA 3, but not the Wagner or Plank (and I no longer own the Doyle). 

The set is 100% graded by PSA.  All HOFers are at least a 6, with many 7.  This set is currently listed #8 on the registry here:    [url]https://www.psacard.com/psasetregistry/baseball/t206-sets/1909-11-t206-complete-player-image-set-wagner-doyle-ny-natl-plank-magie/publishedset/598760[/url]

There are numerous rare backs.  Some Highlights are pictured below

I am open to realistic offers.

Sets 5-8 are all pretty close in set rating.  #7 (happens to be my set) is roughly 16 points better (think 16 commons 1 grade higher generally) based on how PSA weighs the set.  I say zero of that for anything more than context as Ryan could easily put that set in the top 5 if he wanted to.  It's simply a gorgeous set he has and anyone would love to own it!

Congratulations on. Compiling such a beautiful set. As someone who aspires to 520 but not able to reach grades that high, I truly respect and appreciate the joy it must have brought you. What a life adventure!
